# EchoSight 
**AI-Powered Assistive Device for the Visually Impaired**  

## Overview  
EchoSight is an **AI-driven assistive technology** that enhances navigation and safety for visually impaired individuals. By integrating **face recognition, object detection, and obstacle sensing**, it converts visual information into **real-time audio feedback**, making the environment more accessible.  

## Features  
- **Real-time Image Capture** ‚Äì Captures frames using **ESP32-CAM**  
- **Face Recognition** ‚Äì Identifies known faces using **Dlib**  
- **Object Detection** ‚Äì Utilizes **YOLOv4-Tiny** for object identification  
- **Obstacle Detection** ‚Äì Detects nearby obstacles using an **ultrasonic sensor**  
- **Audio Feedback** ‚Äì Converts detected information into **speech output** via **Text-to-Speech (TTS)**  

## Hardware Requirements  
- **ESP32-CAM** ‚Äì Captures images for processing  
- **NodeMCU ESP8266** ‚Äì Handles communication and processing  
- **Ultrasonic Sensor (HC-SR04)** ‚Äì Detects obstacles within **2 meters**  
- **Voltage Divider** ‚Äì Ensures compatibility between components  
- **Portable Battery Pack** ‚Äì Powers the system  

## Software Requirements  
- **Python 3.8+**  
- **OpenCV** ‚Äì Image processing  
- **Dlib** ‚Äì Face recognition  
- **YOLOv4-Tiny** ‚Äì Object detection  
- **Pyttsx3** ‚Äì Text-to-Speech engine  
- **Arduino IDE** ‚Äì For flashing firmware onto **NodeMCU ESP8266**  
- **Firmware Libraries:** ESP32-CAM support, WiFi libraries  

